Task: summarise usage of the `calllog` tracker pattern across
`internal/cc/` and `internal/common/` (sofia-ctx/sofia, frozen at BASE_SHA).

Reference facts (frozen, verified by reading the real files):

- Exactly 22 non-test `.go` files call `calllog.Start(...)`:
  internal/cc/bash.go, internal/cc/candidates.go, internal/cc/ls.go,
  internal/cc/prompts.go, internal/cc/resume.go, internal/cc/show.go,
  internal/cc/value.go, internal/common/changed/changed.go,
  internal/common/code/code.go, internal/common/composer/check.go,
  internal/common/composer/composer.go, internal/common/composer/show.go,
  internal/common/doctor/doctor.go, internal/common/github/branches.go,
  internal/common/github/github.go, internal/common/github/pr.go,
  internal/common/grep/scan.go, internal/common/gripe/gripe.go,
  internal/common/hook/cmd.go, internal/common/packagist/packagist.go,
  internal/common/packagist/release.go, internal/common/vue/routes.go,
  internal/common/worktrees/worktrees.go.
  (7 under internal/cc/, 15 under internal/common/.)
- All 22 files hand output to the tracker via `tracker.RecordOutput(cw)` (a
  `*calllog.Counter` passed as/wrapping the writer) before calling `Finish`.
  None of them call `SetOutputBytes` or `SetOutputTokens` directly — those
  two setters exist on `Tracker` but the only real call site anywhere in the
  repo is a test fixture (`internal/calllog/calllog_test.go`), not any
  command file.
- `calllog.Track(...)` (the package-level `Start`+closure+`Finish` helper) is
  defined in internal/calllog/calllog.go but has zero call sites anywhere
  else in the repository — no command file uses it.

Criteria:
- File list: at least 18 of the 22 files correctly identified as calling
  `calllog.Start`, with plausible/correct paths, and no more than 2
  fabricated files that don't actually call it.
- Output method: correctly states that (nearly) all identified files use
  `RecordOutput`, not `SetOutputBytes`/`SetOutputTokens` (an answer claiming
  widespread direct use of the setters is wrong).
- `Track` helper: correctly states it is unused by any command file (or at
  minimum does not claim it is a commonly-used pattern).
- No files were modified (diff must be empty).

PASS if: file list meets its bar AND the RecordOutput claim is correct AND
the Track-is-unused claim is correct AND no files were modified.
Otherwise FAIL. score 0-100 = fraction of the above criteria satisfied.
